						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the eastern parapet wall of the Jambu-tērtha tank.</p>						

						<p>PLAVA, 1721 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year Plava, Vaiyāśī 5 corresponding to 5th May, 3 Friday, 1661 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It refers to the construction of the <hi rend="italic">nāṭaka-śāla</hi> (auditorium for dramas) of Vijayaranga Chokkanātha by <hi rend="italic">Pāṭakam</hi> Vayimda(pa)ya, the son of <hi rend="italic">Śikshaka</hi> Veṅkaṭēśvaraya. (<hi rend="italic">c.f.</hi> No. B. 48 of 1936.)</p>						

						</summary>
